Cloud Scheduler 0.3

## INTRODUCTION
Cloud management functions and structures are kept in the cloud_management.py file. Cloud scheduler functionality is kept in the cloud_scheduler.py file.

The sample_cloud file is a configuration file of the format currently being processed by the cloud scheduler. The file contains an explanation of its data formatting.

For more documentation on the cloud scheduler, please refer to the following wiki pages:

https://wiki.gridx1.ca/twiki/bin/view/Main/VirtualizationProjectHome#Cloud_Scheduling


## PREREQUISITES
pyXML
suds (https://fedorahosted.org/suds/)

You can install these on RHEL5 (and clones) with the following

# yum install PyXML
# wget 'https://fedorahosted.org/suds/attachment/wiki/WikiStart/python-suds-0.3.6-1.el5.noarch.rpm?format=raw'
# yum localinstall python-suds-0.3.6-1.el5.noarch.rpm?format=raw


On Mac OS X, using Macports, you can install these with the following:
(say you're using python 2.6)
# sudo port install py26-xml py26-suds


## INSTALL
To install cloud scheduler, as root, run:

# python setup.py install


